    "seeker",
    "employer",
    "observer"
  ],
  "observations": [
    "Two-field search (What + Where) occupies nearly half the home screen — dominant primary input surface",
    "Inline company rating (stars + review count) embedded in each job card, clickable to open reviews",
    "Job card is minimalist: title, company+location line, highlighted salary, 3-4 description bullets, single primary Apply CTA plus Save/Share icons",
    "Progressive disclosure on detail: hero with badges (Full-time/Remote/Urgently hiring), then description, then structured Benefits/Requirements/Responsibilities sections, then About-the-company block",
    "Saved searches are first-class: named subscription with per-item push toggle and badge on Find Jobs tab for new results",
    "Sponsored jobs explicitly labeled and segregated from organic Jobs-for-you feed",
    "Company profile uses rating breakdown across 5 axes (work-life / compensation / management / culture / opportunities) plus filterable reviews (All/Positive/Negative/Former/Current)",
    "Resume is a single unified document auto-attached to every Quick Apply — no per-application customization surface",
    "Application tracker is visually thin: 'viewed' status and silence are the dominant states — weak post-apply feedback loop",
    "App-install interstitial on web is a documented anti-pattern forcing mobile-app adoption",
    "AI relevance filter silently removes up to 90% of matches with no user control — opaque algorithmic gate",
    "No ghost-job reporting mechanism — stale listings persist without user-driven expiry signal",
    "Bottom tab bar with 5 destinations: Home / Find Jobs / Messages / My Jobs / Profile — My Jobs acts as dual tracker for saved + applied"
  ]
}